title._content: Henry Squires, American tenor in the Lyster Opera Company, repertoire, ca. 1867-1870 / photographer Sydney and Melbourne Fine Art Photographic Co.

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales

description._content: Squires sang in one of Australia's earliest opera companies. His repertoire of 44 roles by 20 composers would be impossible today with specialisation, higher standards of performance and completeness. Without government funding the company prospered for several decades.
